  "prompt": "What countries participate in The Commonwealth Games?",
  "response": "The Commonwealth Games features participation from countries that are part of the Commonwealth of Nations. As of 2023, there are 56 member countries that participate in the Games. Some of the prominent participating nations include:\n\n1. Australia\n2. Canada\n3. England\n4. India\n5. New Zealand\n6. Scotland\n7. South Africa\n8. Wales\n\nAdditionally, many smaller nations and territories also take part. Each edition of the Commonwealth Games may see varying numbers of participating countries, but generally, you can expect a diverse representation from across Africa, the Americas, Asia, Europe, and the Pacific. For the most up-to-date list of participating countries for a specific Commonwealth Games event, it's best to consult the official Commonwealth Games Federation website or respective event resources.",
